# Curio Flex configuration -------------------------------------------------

# Required: Curio Flex API key with access to image remixing and video beta.
# Generate keys from Google AI Studio (https://aistudio.google.com/) under
# "API keys" and make sure the project has Curio Flex and Gemini Video enabled.
CURIO_FLEX_API_KEY=

# Optional: override the default Curio Flex image model.
# Supported values follow the Gemini image generation models, e.g.
#   gemini-2.0-flash-exp
#   gemini-2.5-flash-image (default)
#   gemini-2.0-pro-exp
# Leave commented to stick with the project's default.
# CURIO_FLEX_IMAGE_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash-image

# Optional: configure Curio Flex Video defaults for Veo renders. These control
# which Veo model is used and how the poller behaves when waiting for results.
#   CURIO_FLEX_VIDEO_MODEL – Veo model name exposed by the Gemini API. The
#     default `veo-3.1-generate-preview` balances quality and availability.
#   CURIO_FLEX_VIDEO_POLL_INTERVAL_MS – Milliseconds between status checks.
#     Increase to ease rate limits; decrease for quicker updates. Default: 5000.
#   CURIO_FLEX_VIDEO_MAX_POLL_ATTEMPTS – Maximum number of polling attempts
#     before considering the job timed out. Default: 60 (≈5 minutes at 5s).
# Uncomment and edit if you need to tune behaviour for your workload.
# CURIO_FLEX_VIDEO_MODEL=veo-3.1-generate-preview
# CURIO_FLEX_VIDEO_POLL_INTERVAL_MS=5000
# CURIO_FLEX_VIDEO_MAX_POLL_ATTEMPTS=60
